verbose_text: In oocytes expressing human TRPP3, injection of diC 8 PIP2, a H 2 O-soluble dioctanoyl analog of PIP2, significantly reduced Ca 2+ -activated TRPP3 channel activity at -50 mV to 28% +/- 4% (XREF_FIG).
